Actionable findings

src/cli.ts
- Consolidate duplicated failure handling and JSON emission in runAgent:
  - The turn.failed and error branches are nearly identical and also duplicate the final “agent.result” JSON emission used in multiple places (failure, aborted, completed). Extract helpers:
    - emitEvent(agentIdx, prompt, event) – single place to JSONL-emit any ThreadEvent when --json
    - emitAgentResult({agent, prompt, status, threadId, usage, error, finalResponse}) – single place to emit the summary line
    - finalizeFailure(message) – builds and returns the AgentResult plus emits JSON summary if requested
  - This will cut conditional duplication and make future changes safer.

- Prevent accidental clearing of finalResponse in updateFinalResponse:
  - Currently updates on item.started, item.updated, and item.completed for agent_message. If item.started for agent_message has empty or undefined text, it can wipe the current finalResponse. Tighten the guard to only update on item.updated/item.completed and only when event.item.text is a non-empty string:
    - if ((event.type === "item.updated" || event.type === "item.completed") && event.item.type === "agent_message" && event.item.text) return event.item.text;

- Reduce parameter sprawl in runAgent:
  - Pass a single options object (e.g., { codex, task, threadOptions, signal, json }) or capture json and threadOptions in a closure where tasks are created. This improves readability and makes it easier to extend parameters without touching call sites.

- Ensure output directory exists before writing:
  - Writing to a nested path with -o can fail if parent dirs don’t exist. Before writeFile, do:
    - const outPath = resolve(config.output);
    - await mkdir(dirname(outPath), { recursive: true });
    - await writeFile(outPath, …)

- Avoid recomputing resolve(config.output):
  - Compute once (const outPath = resolve(config.output)) and reuse for writeFile and the “Wrote results to …” message.

- Strengthen prompt validation in parseCliArgs:
  - Disallow empty or whitespace-only prompts by trimming and filtering. Error if none remain. This avoids launching no-op agents:
    - const prompts = rawPrompts.map(p => p.trim()).filter(Boolean); if (!help && prompts.length === 0) throw …

- Add -h alias for --help:
  - In parseArgs options.help, add short: "h" for a standard UX improvement.

- Make describeEvent exhaustive or add a safe fallback:
  - New Codex item types could appear and currently return null silently. Either add a default case that emits a generic progress line, or add a never check to surface unhandled types during development.

- Minor I/O ergonomics:
  - When printing help on error, you currently write both the error and help to stderr, which is good. For consistency, also add a trailing newline after help in the help path (stdout) so terminals end with a clean prompt.

- Packaging clarity (optional but reduces confusion):
  - package.json "bin" points to src/cli.ts (TypeScript, Bun shebang) while build outputs dist/cli.js. If you intend to publish a compiled artifact, point bin to dist/cli.js post-build. If you intend Bun-only execution from TS, remove build step or clarify in README. This avoids users installing a package that builds a JS file that isn’t wired to the bin.

src/cli.test.ts
- Add tests for edge cases in parseCliArgs:
  - Empty/whitespace prompts are rejected.
  - -h/--help path returns help and does not require prompts.
  - Conflicting --full-auto with --sandbox workspace-write throws the intended error.
  - --cwd resolves to an absolute path when provided.

- Add rendering tests for single-agent cases:
  - Success trims trailing newlines.
  - Failure shows “Error: …”.

- Add JSON summary test for a failed agent:
  - Ensure error is included and status is "failed" and finalResponse is preserved.

These changes simplify control flow, reduce duplication, harden input handling, and make the CLI more maintainable without changing user-visible behavior (except improved validation and -h).
